Cell[TextData[{
 "In the course we looked at how knowledge can be viewed as a collection of \
knowledge components, in the most primitive case these were \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]data\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], connected by link \
representing informational connections between the nodes. Suppose we have a \
knowledge network with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "173df8e4-5b1b-4b9b-8511-7319291c3d00"],
 " where every node has a probability of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"1", "/", "m"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "866afb09-f097-4e5a-91c1-db1ad8a60cc3"],
 " to be connected by an outgoing link to any of the other nodes, and for \
these links to have a weight which is randomly drawn from a probability \
distribution of your choice which leaves the probability of the weight being \
negative less than 5%. There should be no self-loops!"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7482477102982593`*^9, 3.7482477777691245`*^9}, 
   3.748248051980051*^9, {3.7528209990384245`*^9, 3.7528210432087717`*^9}, {
   3.7529215018636885`*^9, 3.752921564396706*^9}, {3.7529216282277703`*^9, 
